            <section>
               <id root="ebccf053-c967-415c-85e8-65dc5ee7ee3f"/>
               <code code="34093-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="REFERENCES SECTION"/>
               <title>REFERENCES</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>1. American Dental Association, Council on Dental Therapeutics, Fluoride compounds, In: Accepted Dental Therapeutics, Ed. 40, Chicago, ADA, 405-407 (1984).  2.  H.R. Englander et al., Clinical Anticaries Effect of Repeated Topical Sodium Fluoride Applications by Mouthpieces, JADA, <content styleCode="underline">75,</content> 638-644 (1967).  3.  H.R. Englander et al., Residual Anticaries Effect of Repeated Topical Sodium Fluoride Applications by Mouthpieces, JADA, <content styleCode="underline">78,</content> 783-787 (1969).  4.  H.R. Englander et al., Incremental Rates of Dental Caries After Repeated Topical Sodium Fluoride Applications in Children With Lifelong Consumption of Fluoridated Water, JADA, <content styleCode="underline">82,</content> 354-358, (1971).</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">You should call your doctor for medical advice about serious adverse events.  To report a serious adverse event or obtain product information, contact Cypress Pharmaceutical, Inc. at 1-800-793-2145 or FDA at 1-800-FDA-1088 (Toll Free). </content>
                  </paragraph>
